  <p>
    When I write up these tournaments I always feel like I should add some deep reason for them, but let’s be honest, nobody wants the recipe-blog life story.
  </p>

  <p>
    BEHOLD! THE HEADLESS HORSMAN!
  </p>

  <ul style="text-align:left;">
    <li>A circle is inscribed on the ground. Move around it freely.</li>
    <li>Once a foot steps into the circle, that foot cannot leave.</li>
    <li>Leaving the circle forfeits the touch.</li>
    <li>Only head shots count.</li>
    <li>After a point, reset outside the circle.</li>
    <li>Touches starting from outside the circle (lunging in) don’t count.</li>
    <li>Bout structure: best of 5 touches keeps it quick and lively.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This one only works with gentle fencers or very forgiving weapons. Single stick feels right, but you do you.
  </p>

  <p style="text-align:center; font-weight:600; margin-top:1rem;">
    Have fun and prove it with iron
  </p>
